msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/ops/common-problems/security-issues/index.rst:524
msgid ""
"If you suspect problems with mutual TLS, first ensure that `Citadel is "
"healthy <#repairing-citadel>`_, and second ensure that `keys and "
"certificates are being delivered <#keys-and-certificates-errors>`_ to "
"sidecars properly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/ops/common-problems/security-issues/index.rst:529
msgid ""
"If everything appears to be working so far, the next step is to verify "
"that the right `authentication policy "
"</docs/tasks/security/authentication/authn-policy/>`_ is applied and the "
"right destination rules are in place."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/ops/common-problems/security-issues/index.rst:537
msgid "Citadel is not behaving properly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/ops/common-problems/security-issues/index.rst:541
msgid "Workloads with new Kubernetes service accounts can not"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/ops/common-problems/security-issues/index.rst:542
msgid ""
"be started when Citadel is disabled for maintenance since they can’t get "
"their certificates generated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/ops/common-problems/security-issues/index.rst:545
msgid ""
"Citadel is not a critical data plane component. The default workload "
"certificate lifetime is 3 months. Certificates will be rotated by Citadel"
" before they expire. If Citadel is disabled for short maintenance "
"periods, existing mutual TLS traffic will not be affected."
msgstr ""

